                  "$type": "Models.Core.Folder, Models",
                  "ShowInDocs": false,
                  "Name": "ThinzarExperiment",
                  "ResourceName": null,
                  "Children": [
                    {
                      "$type": "Models.Documentation, Models",
                      "Text": "The simulations in this folder aim to replicate the experiment conducted by [#ThinzarSoeBlaclMoot], with a primary focus on Perennial Ryegrass and White Clover monocultures under nitrogen‑plus and nitrogen‑minus treatments. This folder contains multiple experiments built using two pasture modelling frameworks namely AGPasture and Pasture Model. Both models are used to explore differences in growth and yield under constrasting nitrogen treatments for Perennial Ryegrass. AGPasture is used for White Colver. Defoliation is implemented using AgPasture's SimpleGrazing and Management operations for scheduled defoliation. The defoliation, irriation and fertilisation events are consistent with the original experiment.\n\nThe experiment is set up under the following conditions:\n1. Location: Lincoln, New Zealand\n2. Clock: 1/03/2017 - 30/06/2021\n3. Soil: The soil was a Wakanui silt loam with medium fertility\n4. Sowing date: 2017-03-31\n5. Irrigation: Followed the schedule provided\n6. Fertilisation: Followed the schedule provided\n7. Defoliation: Followed the schedule\n8. Report variables: Biomass, LAI, NConc and NDVI\n8. Observed Excel: ThinzarObserved.xlsx",
                      "Name": "Documentation",
                      "ResourceName": null,
                      "Children": [],
                      "Enabled": true,
                      "ReadOnly": false
                    },
                    {
